Reasoning: The paper deals with compliance in the context of session behaviours, which is a formalism interpreting session types into a subset of CCS without τ. This makes it likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the formalisation of operational semantics via a LTS, which is a common topic in Programming Languages (cs.PL) sub-category. The paper also deals with client/server architectures and compliance, which falls under the Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-category. The paper also discusses decision procedures and axiomatic systems, which are topics in Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with compliance and protocols, which is a topic in Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
